body:
"(laughs) who is Asheck Blessing? She is a gospel minister, born and bred in the Northwest region of Cameroon, precisely Mbengwi..." A subtle blend of education and music, Asheck is a "diamond in the rough".  Though a student at COVICOM, Blessing's music streak cannot go unnoticed.

The great talent is inspired by personal experiences, her darling mother, Tasha Cobbs, Jekalin Carr, and Ada. Don't you just love them too?

 "..I was born to do music...In 5yrs, I aspire to reach the ends of the world with my music..." Despite the financial constraints, Asheck will not let her background put her back on the ground. That is to say, her determination is her driving force.

United we stand, divided we fall"; Asheck believes lack of unity amongst gospel artists is a plague in Cameroon.  "... Cameroon should support their own...they should create platforms and show more respect towards gospel artists..."
For those who don't know why they are into gospel music, here's a cue:
  "...I am not doing gospel music for fame...or money...I think God is passing through me to speak to people..."
